\begin{abstract}
We outline a connection between scalar quark confinement, a
phenomenologically successful concept heretofore lacking fundamental
justification, and QCD.  Although scalar confinement does not follow from
QCD, there is an interesting and close relationship between them. We
develop a simple model intermediate between scalar confinement and the QCD
string for illustrative purposes.  Finally, we find the bound state masses
of scalar, time-component vector, and string confinement analytically
through semi-classical quantization.
\end{abstract}
